  "timeboxMinutes": 30,
  "prompt": "Finance wants to reconcile card transactions against approved trips.\n\nWrite `match_transactions_to_trips(base_url, token)`. Fetch all transactions and all trips. Return a mapping from transaction id to trip id for transactions whose date falls inside a trip for the same employee.\n\nA transaction matches a trip when:\n\n- `txn[\"employee_id\"] == trip[\"employee_id\"]`\n- `trip[\"start_date\"] <= txn_date <= trip[\"end_date\"]`\n\nUse only the date portion of the transaction timestamp: `txn[\"timestamp\"][:10]`.\n\nReturn contract:\n\n- Return `dict[str, str]`, shaped like `{\"txn_001\": \"trip_001\"}`.\n- Keys are transaction ids. Values are trip ids.\n- Skip transactions outside all trips.\n- If multiple trips for the same employee overlap and both match, choose the first matching trip returned by the trips API.\n- If there are no matches, return `{}`.\n\nEndpoint details:\n\n- `GET /v1/transactions` is paginated and requires auth.\n- `GET /v1/trips` is paginated, requires auth, and may return `429` with `Retry-After`; retry the same trips request after a `429`.\n\nThe test harness passes `token` into your function. Do not define or hardcode it; use the `token` parameter when building the `Authorization` header.\n\nInvariants and corner cases:\n\n- Start and end dates are inclusive.\n- Same date but wrong employee is not a match.\n- A one-day trip matches transactions on that date.\n- Do not advance the trips cursor after a 429.\n\nShared fake API note: this uses the in-process `requests` mock described in the Ramp Travel module guide; there is no real network.\n\nValidation focus: same-employee join, inclusive date boundaries, one-day trips, no outside matches, overlapping-trip tie behavior, and 429 handling.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "matchTransactionsToTrips",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "base_url",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "token",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      }
    ],
    "output": {
      "type": "object"
    }
  },
